The paper deals with the problem of sparsity pattern recovery in compressive sensing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses probabilistic models and derives bounds, which are techniques commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistics (cs.SI).
